            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>A New Emancipation Scheme</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>SS is complaining about a call for a Northern convention on emancipation.
                    Sees no possible solutions: Colonization won't work, neither will shipping
                    slaves to the North.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Constitutional Reform</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>No argument is needed to prove the miserable working of the system under
                    which the governement, in all its departments, has been growing worse and worse
                    for the last five or six years.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Richmond Whig and Lynchburg Virginian are calling for a new State
                    Constitution, revising the 1851 version. SS agrees, citing inefficiency, rising
                    crime, poor judiciating. But a Convention might not solve the problems, since it
                    would likely be dominated by Democrats.</summary>
            </div>
